  "description": "In Part 2, Sam leaves the mountains and training environment of Montana and heads off to Europe where he comes face-to-face with the Foe.  He used raw guts and trickery to convince a platoon of Germans to surrender to Sam and his wounded fire team partner.  On his way back, he stops to rescue three soldiers that had been pinned down by the very platoon he had captured. Sam goes on to describe his peace-time service with the Royal Canadian [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>In Part 2, Sam leaves the mountains and training environment of Montana and heads off to Europe where he comes face-to-face with the Foe.  He used raw guts and trickery to convince a platoon of Germans to surrender to Sam and his wounded fire team partner.  On his way back, he stops to rescue three soldiers that had been pinned down by the very platoon he had captured.</p>\n<p>Sam goes on to describe his peace-time service with the <a title=\"The Royal Canadian Regiment\" href=\"http://www.theroyalcanadianregiment.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">Royal Canadian Regiment</a> and his dedication to the Airborne.</p>\n<p>Follow me on Twitter @MikeLacroix32</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-372-50\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CMHP-Episode-015-WO2-Sam-Magee-Part-2.mp3?_=50\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CMHP-Episode-015-WO2-Sam-Magee-Part-2.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CMHP-Episode-015-WO2-Sam-Magee-Part-2.mp3</a></audio>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/img_0660.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-373\" alt=\"img_0660\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/img_0660-200x300.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/img_0660-200x300.jpg 200w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/img_0660.jpg 680w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sam is always proud to represent the 1st Special Service Force at reunions.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/get-item-image.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"get-item-image\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/get-item-image-194x300.jpg\" width=\"194\" height=\"300\" /></a></p>\n<p>Cpl Sam Magee, wearing his US Jump Wings, earned with the 1st SSF</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/William_Magee_3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-374\" alt=\"William_Magee_3\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/William_Magee_3-288x300.jpg\" width=\"288\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/William_Magee_3-288x300.jpg 288w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/William_Magee_3.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 288px) 100vw, 288px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sgt Sam Magee, Airborne Paratrooper</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Demon.gif\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-375\" alt=\"Demon\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Demon.gif\" width=\"226\" height=\"283\" /></a></p>\n<p>The unofficial insignia of the 1st SSF</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103820_41b599a1ea_o.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-376\" alt=\"3064103820_41b599a1ea_o\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103820_41b599a1ea_o-214x300.jpg\" width=\"214\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103820_41b599a1ea_o-214x300.jpg 214w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3064103820_41b599a1ea_o.jpg 551w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 214px) 100vw, 214px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sgt Sam Magee of the Royal Canadian Regiment</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3083990039_87de5ab82e_o.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-377\" alt=\"3083990039_87de5ab82e_o\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3083990039_87de5ab82e_o-207x300.jpg\" width=\"207\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3083990039_87de5ab82e_o-207x300.jpg 207w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3083990039_87de5ab82e_o.jpg 395w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 207px) 100vw, 207px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Sam, dedicated to physical fitness</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
